</P>
<P>
   The court sustained five charges brought by the Association of
the Bar of the City of New York that Nixon had obstructed ``the due
administration of justice'' and thus violated the Code of
Professional Responsibility, a set of rules that all lawyers are
required to observe. The charges weren't contested by Nixon.
</P>
<P>
   In its 4-to-1 opinion, the court, which had admitted Nixon to
practice law in New York in 1963, found that the charges were
substantiated by documentary evidence, such as the tapes of Nixon
himself, excerpts of testimony of individuals given to various
congressional committees, and affidavits.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Who is credited with writing the song ``Happy Birthday''?
</P>
<P>
   A: Facts on File Encyclopedia of Word and Phrase Origins
explains that it was written in 1893 by Patty Smith Hill
(1868-1946) and Mildred Jane Hill (1859-1916) as part of their
``Song Stories for the Kindergarten.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's the background on Atlanta Braves rookie shortstop
Rafael Furcal? A recent article described him as a candidate for
