   HOME&AMP;GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   HOME-POOL _ Jim and Edie Duane had a shopping list of features
when they set out to create an outdoor living space in their back
yard. And not all of them were in sync. Jim, who swam competitively
in his youth, wanted a pool for exercise. Edie, an avid gardener,
didn't want a big aqua rectangle to overpower her landscape. He
wanted a detached home office. She had her heart set on a guest
house that would double as a cabana. Through careful planning, the
Duanes created a versatile setting behind their Alpharetta area
home that meets all their needs. Plenty of others are opting for
pool-centered environments as they extend their homes to outdoors
where they can exercise, relax, garden and entertain.(Flanders,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NUTS-AND-BOLTS _ Draining a soggy walkway, identifying termites
