   FLA-TOBACCO-TRIAL (Miami) _ As lawyers in a federal courtroom
here fight over the fate of tobacco companies, many people in the
audience are painfully aware of their own fate. Ex-smokers who are
party to the class action suit watch the trial every day, their
wheezing and the clicks of their respirators punctuating the
testimony. By Rick Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-TURTLES-FISHING (Undated) _ Scientists say that a number of
factors, chiefly commercial fishing, have doomed Pacific
leatherback turtles, which are already nearly extinct. By Henry
Fountain.
