<P>
   DRUG-PRICES (Washington) _ Private insurance has increasingly
been picking up the cost of prescription medicine for Americans,
who now pay only about one-quarter of their total drug costs out of
pocket. That explains why there is no general political uproar
although drug prices in the United States have been rising by as
much as 15 percent a year, pharmaceutical manufacturers are among
the most profitable businesses in the world and many new drugs in
Canada and Europe cost a fraction of what they do in the United
States. By David E. Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   MINN-WELFARE (Washington) _ A large-scale study of Minnesota
welfare reform has noted higher earnings and income, less poverty,
an increase in marriage rates and marital stability and
improvements in children's behavior and school performance _ a
positive combination never seen before. By Robert Pear.
