panels that make up ``Synapsis Shuffle,'' Robert Rauschenberg's
latest work, are meant to be assembled by a different group of
people every time they are shown, so the work will never be seen
the same way twice. By Carol Vogel.
</P>
<P>
   BOLSHOI-U.S. (Washington) _ The Bolshoi Ballet returned to the
United States for the first time in more than a decade this week,
and opened its tour at the Kennedy Center with a performance of
``Romeo and Juliet.'' By Anna Kisselgoff.
