SAN FRANCISCO _  CHICKEN  _ I used to be a devout chicken-lover,
always eager to include it in casual and special meals. But it
became too accessible. Chicken had become boring. So, I salvaged my
relationship by asking some of the Bay Area's top chefs what they
do to keep chicken interesting. 
Main story followed by 3 sidebars and recipes. 
 By Tilde Herrera  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; SECRET-PASTA &LR;  _ Delfina chef Craig Stoll shows how
easy it is to create magnificent orecchiette pasta with a sauce
made from parsley, chile flakes, garlic and anchovy fillets. Potato
and broccoli rabe are added for an interesting twist. It's a dish
that is fast enough for a weeknight dinner, but complex enough for
a dinner party.
<P>
   This is the latest installment of the regular column describing
what makes a Bay Area restaurant's dish a success, we'll tell how
to make it.
