SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; MORELS &LR;  _ Wild king boletes and rumple-headed
morels can sell for $45 a pound or more in Bay Area markets _ a
prospect that makes gathering your own an attractive alternative.
To the uninitiated, how and where to search _ and even what to hunt
for _ remains as much a mystery as the morels themselves. But for
those dedicated enough to camp out in the woods and tromp through
old burns and slag in search of springtime mushrooms, an organized
foray is the way to go.
</P>
