   CIR-WEATHER-ONLINE (Undated) _ Carey Hoffman describes himself
as a weather nut. Since he was 9 years old and a tornado touched
down one block from his house in the suburbs of Cincinnati, Mr.
Hoffman has been in pursuit of information about the weather. ``The
day we got cable TV was a great day,'' said Hoffman, who saw his
first radar screen displaying weather information on a local cable
channel. The debut of the Weather Channel in 1982 was another
bright day for Hoffman. But it is the Internet that has made
Hoffman and others like him feel as if they are in weather
paradise. By Bonnie Rothman Morris.
