say. Although fans of ultraviolent first-person shooter games
helped establish the culture of online gaming, there now is an
entirely new ruling class. These days, Internet gamers are not some
clan of elusive teenage demons. More likely, they are Mom and Dad,
playing games like hearts and bingo. By David Kushner.
