   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; SRILANKA-TOLL-ART (Colombo) _ Hailed at midcentury as one of a
few third-world countries most likely to succeed, this
once-promising island nation has instead sacrificed more than
60,000 of its 19 million people, made refugees of nearly a million
others, and forfeited its chances of serious economic development.
By Indira Lakshmanan. 1,300 words. GRAPHIC
</P>
<P>
   FIJI-ANALYSIS (Undated) _ A side issue of the Fiji uprising is a
history of racial conflict between indigenous Fijians and
descendants of Indians who were brought to the island by the
British. By Charles Radin. 900 words.
</P>
