<HEADLINE>
HOW THE SACAGAWEA DOLLAR IMAGE CAME TO BE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Who designed the woman and child on the Sacagawea
dollar coin? _ W.D., Carlsbad, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The image was created by artist Glenna Goodacre, who
also sculpted the Vietnam Women's Memorial in Washington, D.C.
</P>
<P>
   Sacagawea, a Shoshone Indian who assisted Meriwether Lewis and
William Clark on their journey from the Northern Great Plains to
the Pacific Ocean in 1804-1806, is portrayed with her son Jean
Baptiste.
</P>
<P>
   There are no documented pictures of Sacagawea, so Goodacre
recruited as a model Randy'L Teton, 23, an arts student and member
of the Shoshone-Bannock tribe from the Fort Hall Indian Reservation
in Idaho.
</P>
<P>
   Goodacre, a West Texas native with residences in Sante Fe, N.M.,
and Dallas, is the mother of model Jill Goodacre Connick. She has a
Web site at www.glennagoodacre.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ What is the name of the ``Frugal Gourmet'' TV show
theme music? _ E.C.F., Hurst
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The theme was the bourree from Georg Friedrich Handel's
``Water Music Suite No. 1 in F Major,'' according to Tom Warda,
publisher of a Web site devoted to Jeff ``Frugal Gourmet'' Smith.
</P>
<P>
   The bourree, a dance within the overall composition, is included
on the Classical Treasures CD ``Best of Handel'' by
Madacy/Duplicate Numbers and many other Handel collections.
</P>
<P>
   One place that offers ``Best of Handel'' is the classical and
jazz retailer CD Choice. Call (800) 648-2224 or visit the Web site
www.cdchoice.com.
</P>
<P>
   An audio clip of the theme is available on Warda's site,
www.angelfire.com/ca2/twarda.
</P>
<P>
   .MDNM/Q:.MDNM/ Where can I write to June Allyson? _ E.W., Krum
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to her in care of the June Allyson Foundation,
1200 19th St., N.W., Suite 300, Washington, DC 20036.
</P>
<P>
   The foundation, which is administrated by the American
Urogynecologic Society, was established to support medical research
and educational efforts that advance incontinence care.
</P>
<P>
   Allyson, 82, has been a member of the Federal Council on Aging
since 1987. She has an official Web site at www.juneallyson.com.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
