</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-EXECUTE (Dallas) _ Gov. George W. Bush of Texas said
Wednesday that he was considering a temporary grant of clemency for
a man scheduled to be executed on Thursday so that DNA evidence in
the case could be tested. It would be the first such stay that he
has issued as governor. On Tuesday a state appeals court overruled
a trial judge's order allowing a delay for DNA testing in the case
of Ricky McGinn, who was convicted of raping and killing his
12-year-old stepdaughter. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
