<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dupri has a keeper in first soundtrack
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Atlanta producer-rapper-label president Jermaine Dupri's first
soundtrack has the kind of singles that last. It begins with a
remix of a song that's already hovered in the Top 10 of the pop,
R&AMP;B and rap charts _ the rubbery ``That's What I'm Looking For'' by
rapper Da Brat. This time her quite capable compadres Missy
``Misdemeanor'' Elliott and Dupri join in.
</P>
<P>
   It introduces a new act on Dupri's So So Def label, named Bow
Wow, which exhibits as much dexterity with a lyric as
million-selling labelmate Da Brat on ``Bounce With Me''; and as
much potential to be a preteen pinup as Dupri's first big find,
Kris Kross.
</P>
<P>
   And most importantly, ``Big Momma's House'' establishes a strong
enough foundation with those first tracks _ including Dupri, Nas
and Monica's kinetic boast over a Peter Gabriel sample
(``Sledgehammer''), ``I've Got to Have It'' _ to weather the
sizable number of weaker offerings that follow (Devin ``I Want to
Kiss You,'' Kurupt, R.O.C. &AMP; Phats Bgossi's ``Radio'').
</P>
<P>
   _Sonia Murray
</P>
<P>
   'Big Momma's House' Soundtrack
</P>
<P>
   Various artists / So So Def-Sony / 14 tracks / Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : More on ``Big Momma's House'' and So So Def
Recordings: www.bigmommashousemovie.com and www.sosodef.com
</P>
