<HEADER>
A0911 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-VIDEO-MOON01-COX     05-31 0332
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MOON01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Carrey embodies late comic Kaufman
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A dizzying look at the mind of comic genius Andy Kaufman, capped
by Jim Carrey's spectacular lead performance.
</P>
<P>
   Carrey's impersonation of the late, prankish Kaufman, a
performer as interested in making people squirm as making them
laugh, is often so pitch-perfect, it's more like channeling than
acting. The movie's title comes from an R.E.M. song about the
comic, and the Athens band wrote the movie's score.
</P>
<P>
   `Man on the Moon'
</P>
<P>
   Rated R / Our critic's grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B :For the Andy Kaufman fan site:
www.andykaufman.jvlnet.com
</P>
<P>
   OTHER NEW RELEASES
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Snow Falling on Cedars'' (PG-13) _ Pretty but chilly. Based
on the best seller, Ethan Hawke plays a newspaperman looking into
slaying charges against a Japanese-American. The case rekindles
memories of internment during World War II and Hawke's youthful
romance with the suspect's wife. Beautifully photographed to mask
its thin plot, ``Cedars'' generates little passion and, frankly, is
flatline drama. Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Miss Julie'' (R) _ A mistake. August Strindberg's late
19th-century play was once considered so controversial that it was
banned in his native Sweden. Today, his study of class warfare
spiced with sexual politics seems merely boring and misogynistic.
The aristocratic Miss Julie (Saffron Burrows) initiates a doomed
flirtation with her father's footman, Jean (Peter Mullan). As the
ambitious servant, Mullan has a suitably arrogant and manipulative
presence but Burrows is lamentably weak as the neurotic and
conflicted Julie. Grade: D
</P>
<P>
   _Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  O N T H E W E B : For upcoming video release dates:
www.comingsoon.net/videos.htm
</P>
<P>
   Steve Murray and Eleanor Ringel Gillespie write for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
