<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Strawberries and cream, in a luscious pie
 &HT;    By Marcia Langherny
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   This sounds like the warm-weather treat requested by Catherine
Potter. She called it Jell-O Parfait Pie, but reader Barbara
Bigelow calls it Strawberry Pie, found in the 1953 edition of the
``Better Homes &AMP; Gardens Cookbook.''
</P>
<P>
   Our tester calls it ``quick, easy, perfect for summer.'' And
that about says it all.
</P>
<P>
   DESSERT
</P>
<P>
   Strawberry Pie
</P>
<P>
   Makes 8 servings
</P>
<P>
   Preparation time: 15 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Chilling time: about 1 hour, divided
</P>
<P>
   1 small (3-ounce) package strawberry-flavored gelatin
</P>
<P>
   1 cup boiling water
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup cold water
</P>
<P>
   1 pint vanilla ice cream, softened
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sliced fresh strawberries
</P>
<P>
   1 (9-inch) pastry shell, baked and cooled, or graham cracker
crust
</P>
<P>
   Whipped cream and fresh strawberries for garnish, if desired
</P>
<P>
   In a medium mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add
cold water and stir well to mix. Cut ice cream into 6 chunks and
add to gelatin mixture. Stir until ice cream melts. Cover and chill
mixture until it starts to thicken and mound when spooned, 20 to 30
minutes. Gently fold in sliced strawberries. Pour into cooled
pastry or graham cracker crust. Chill till firm, 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream and strawberries, if desired.
</P>
<P>
   Per serving: 233 calories, 7 grams protein, 12 grams fat
(percent calories from fat, 45), 26 grams carbohydrates, 15
milligrams cholesterol, 169 milligrams sodium, 1 gram fiber.
</P>
<P>
   Requests
</P>
<P>
   Bonnie Lann is looking for a granola recipe she remembers from
the late '70s that had oats, raisins, sunflower seeds and other
nuts and grains and was bound with sweetened condensed milk.
</P>
<P>
   Chloe Fleenor of Mountain City, Tenn., wants directions for
filling Ritz crackers with peanut butter and coating in white
chocolate.
</P>
<P>
   Contacting this column
</P>
<P>
   Recipes or requests to be published in this column should be
sent to Recipe Swap, Food Department, The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Fax:
404-526-5509. Include a daytime phone number. E-mail:
mlanghenry(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
