<P>
   PHONE-CHARGES _ The FCC and the big telephone companies have
reached an agreement to eliminate some of the back-end charges that
local phone companies charge long distance companies, which should
result in a dramatic rate decrease for customers. We talk with
BellSouth to find out local impact. (Hubbard, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOME-DEPOT _ ATLANTA _ Home Depot holds its annual stockholder
meeting today in metro Atlanta. We'll see who's protesting and
complaining amid the whoops and cheers at this year's show. With
hundreds of stockholders in attendance, HD has one of the most
lively gatherings in the annual meeting circuit. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   CNN-AOL _ WASHINGTON _ Robert W. Pittman, president and chief
operating officer of America Online Inc. and the man who soon will
replace Ted Turner as the head of the cable TV empire, says
employees will see little change. Other highlights from an intervew
Wednesday. (Geewax, Cox News Service)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   LOTUS-KEYNOTE _ The founder of Lotus keynotes Harvard conference
on Internet policy saying that convergence won't mean tvs and
computers, but will mean e-mail and telephones. How will businesses
make that happen? He doesn't know. In fact, he's a venture
capitalist now and he says he won't fund this. Still he says, it
should be done. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ With a judge's ruling on a potential
breakup of Microsoft Corp. expected at any time, the company is
expected to lodge its final objections Wednesday to the
government's proposal. (Glass, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washgton and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   3WOMEN _ Three business women backed by Xerox Corp. are starting
a business and technology center Austin-Bergstrom International
Airport starting July 1. The center will include standard printing,
copying and foreign currency exchange sersvices downstairs and
private business meeting room and lounge upstairs. The idea is to
provide a convenience to business travelers, both those based in
Austin and those traveling here to meet with Austin clients.
(Ladendorf, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
