   PHONE-CHARGES (Washington) _ The Federal government and many of
the nation's leading telephone companies announce an agreement to a
sweeping reshuffling of phone rates that should reduce the bills of
all businesses and consumers. Officials said the reductions, part
of an agreement and an order by the FCC, amounts to the largest
rate cut in the history of federal telephone regulation. By Stephen
Labaton. (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news
