<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MEATLOAF-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAMA MIA! MEATLOAF BRINGS IT ALL BACK HOME
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By NATALIE HAUGHTON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following recipes are for David Hogan who requested what
sounded like an Italian-flavored meatloaf (stuffed with cheese,
mushrooms and Italian aged ham). Barbara Robinson sent along one
that might be close. Although Suzanne Raymond is sharing a very
good recipe, she noted that it isn't exactly the one he requested.
</P>
<P>
   The sounds of the meatloaf brought back memories of a delicious
Italian Meat Roll that I made often some years back. I unearthed
the recipe _ which I adapted _ from Better Homes and Gardens
magazine _ and have also included it today.
</P>
<P>
   So take your pick _ or try them all. Enjoy! &QL; 
MAMA'S ITALIAN MEATLOAF &QL; 
(Shared by Barbara Robinson, Los Angeles) &QL; 
2 pounds lean ground beef &QL; 
1 pound Italian sausage &QL; 
1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs &QL; 
2 eggs, beaten &QL; 
1 medium onion, chopped &QL; 
1 green pepper, chopped &QL; 
1 teaspoon oregano &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon pepper &QL; 
1 clove garlic, minced &QL; 
1 cup pizza sauce &QL; 
1/2 pound thinly sliced prosciutto (Italian ham) &QL; 
8 ounces sliced Provolone OR Swiss cheese (about 3 large slices of
either cheese) &QL; 
1 (8-ounce) can sliced mushrooms, drained
</P>
<P>
   Mix first 10 ingredients together along with 3/4 cup pizza sauce
until well blended.
</P>
<P>
   Pat 1/2 of meat mixture into an oval shape in bottom of an
ungreased 9x13-inch pan. Cover top of meat with prosciutto, cheese
and mushrooms. Top with remaining meat mixture, making certain
sides of meat are sealed by pinching together. Spread top of
meatloaf with remaining 1/4 cup pizza sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 375-degree oven 1 hour 15 minutes. Let stand 5
minutes, then cut into slices to serve. &QL; 
COMPANY MEATLOAF &QL; 
(Shared by Suzanne Raymond, Northridge) &QL; 
STUFFING: &QL; 
1/4 cup (1/2 stick) butter &QL; 
4 ounces sliced mushrooms &QL; 
1 teaspoon lemon juice &QL; 
1 onion, chopped &QL; 
3 cups soft bread crumbs &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon EACH salt and pepper &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon thyme &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning &QL; 
1/4 cup chopped parsley &QL; 
MEAT MIXTURE: &QL; 
2 eggs, beaten &QL; 
2 1/2 pounds lean ground lean beef &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon EACH salt and pepper &QL; 
1/4 cup milk &QL; 
1/3 cup ketchup &QL; 
1 teaspoon dry mustard
</P>
<P>
   For Stuffing, heat butter until melted. Add mushrooms, lemon
juice and onion; saute 3 minutes. Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper,
thyme, poultry seasoning and parsley. Mix well; set aside.
</P>
<P>
   For Meat Mixture, mix together all meat mixture ingredients
until well blended.
</P>
<P>
   Pack 1/2 of meat mixture into a foil-lined 10 by 5 by 3-inch
loaf pan. Cover with all of stuffing. Top with remaining meat
mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 375-degree oven 1 hour 15 minutes or until
done. Brush top with additional ketchup, if desired. Cut into
slices to serve. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ITALIAN MEAT ROLL &QL; 
2 eggs, beaten &QL; 
3/4 cup soft bread crumbs (1 slice bread) &QL; 
1/2 cup tomato sauce &QL; 
2 tablespoons snipped parsley &QL; 
1 teaspoon dried basil, crushed &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon pepper &QL; 
1 small clove garlic, minced &QL; 
2 pounds lean ground beef &QL; 
8 to 10 thin slices salami &QL; 
6 ounces (1 1/2 cups) shredded mozzarella cheese &QL; 
3 slices mozzarella cheese, halved diagonally
</P>
<P>
   Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, parsley, basil, salt,
pepper and garlic. Stir in ground beef; mixing well.
</P>
<P>
   On foil or waxed paper, pat meat to a 12 by 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange salami slices atop meat, leaving a small margin around
edges. Sprinkle shredded cheese over salami. Starting from short
end, carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift; seal edges and
ends.
</P>
<P>
   Place roll, seam side down, in a 13 by 9 by 2-inch baking pan.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 1 hour 15 minutes or until
done. Place cheese wedges over top of roll; return to oven 5
minutes or until cheese melts. With a sharp knife, carefully cut
into slices to serve. Makes 6 servings. &QL; 
-Cook's Corner welcomes recipe requests from readers. While we
cannot reply to them individually, we will answer those of general
interest in this column. Also, if you can help another reader with
a recipe request, write to Cook's Corner, Daily News Food
Department, P.O. Box 4200, Woodland Hills, Calif. 91365-4200.
Please be sure recipes specify exact package sizes, can and pan
sizes and baking times and temperatures.
</P>
<P>
   Recipes printed are from the source indicated and have not been
tested by the Daily News Food Department unless noted.
</P>
