<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JUNE 1
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SOTHEBY-APPOINT-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 30,
about a large shareholder's objections to the election of Robert
Taubman to the board of Sotheby's Holdings, where his father is a
former chairman, misstated the father's given name. He is A. Alfred
Taubman, not Albert.
</P>
<P>
   BC-LIVING-WILLS-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, May 28,
about obstacles faced by patients and families in planning for
peaceful deaths misstated the location of the Center to Improve
Care of the Dying, where the director, Dr. Joanne Lynn, conducted a
large study of patients. It is at the George Washington University
School of Medicine and Health Sciences, not at Georgetown
University.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-CELL-IMPLANTS-NYT (moved on Monday, May 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 29,
about laboratory-grown neural cells misstated the given name of a
doctor who implanted them into the brains of stroke patients. He is
Dr. Douglas Kondziolka, not John.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MARIJUANA-FILM-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 30,
about a movie review of ``Grass,'' a documentary about marijuana,
referred incorrectly to its rating. It is R (Under 17 requires
accompanying parent or adult guardian) _ not unrated.
</P>
